HEADWORD: Padella
<hw>Pa*del"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It., prop., a
pan, a friing pan, fr. L. <ets>patella</ets> a pan.]</ety> <def>A large
cup or deep saucer, containing fatty matter in which a wick is placed,
-- used for public illuminations, as at St. Peter's, in Rome. Called
also <altname>padelle</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

